definition: to set out/to set in motion/the start (of some activity)

to rise/to raise/to get up/to set out/to start/to appear/to launch/to initiate (action)/to draft/to establish/to get (from a depot or counter)/verb suffix, to start/starting from (a time, place, price etc)/classifier for occurrences or unpredictable events: case, instance/classifier for groups: batch, group
a step/a pace/walk/march/stages in a process/situation

sentences.english: Yeah, but it's all starting, a lot of work.
sentences.chinese: 是的，但它已经全面起步了，有大量的工作要做。

sentences.english: Birding is a fun, rewarding hobby that is easy to get started with.
sentences.chinese: 观鸟是一种有趣而有益的爱好，也也很容易起步。

sentences.english: So I'm on the road a bit, and I hold meetings, sometimes at the client's place.
sentences.chinese: 我才刚刚起步，有时候我在客户提供的地点开会。

sentences.english: Nearly all U.S. professional baseball players start their careers in the minor leagues.
sentences.chinese: 几乎所有美国职业棒球球员都是从小联盟起步的。

sentences.english: The driving wheel may slip while starting or speeding up.
sentences.chinese: 在起步或加速时，驱动轮可能会打滑。

sentences.english: The fifth right traffic right in China has started to open up to the outside world.
sentences.chinese: 我国第五航权的开放刚开始起步。

sentences.english: China's aircraft leasing business has an experience of more than 20 years, but still in its infancy.
sentences.chinese: 中国的飞机租赁业历经20余年，仍处于起步阶段。

sentences.english: Wireless trading in Korea predates its introduction in Japan.
sentences.chinese: 无线交易在韩国的起步要早于日本。

sentences.english: The investment of China in Asia started late but developed rapidly.
sentences.chinese: 中国对亚洲地区投资起步晚，发展迅猛。

sentences.english: Driving a vehicle should be a smooth start, quickly shifting action.
sentences.chinese: 驾驶车辆时应做到起步平稳，换挡动作迅速。

sentences.english: The sample above is a trivial variation of the QuickStart app.
sentences.chinese: 上面的例子是《快速起步》应用的一个简单的变体。

sentences.english: Five-year high vocational education in medical college starts late.
sentences.chinese: 医学院校的五年制高职起步晚。

sentences.english: Our tele-medicine start late, but it develops fast.
sentences.chinese: 我军远程医疗起步较晚，但发展较快。

sentences.english: Since the community service industry in Quanzhou city starts late, it develops rapidly.
sentences.chinese: 泉州市的社区服务业起步较迟，但发展很快。

sentences.english: Q. Off the start line into the first corner and the incident with Vettel?
sentences.chinese: 在起步线之后的第一个弯角你与瓦特尔有一个小事故？

sentences.english: Releasing Tenzin Delek and his supporters would be a good start.
sentences.chinese: 释放丹增德勒和他的支持者是一个很好的起步。
